result.execSummary:
The defendant Michael Henry Paul Merrill was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Michael Henry Paul Merrill is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Michael Henry Paul Merrill was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "B"], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Apprs: CO: SRN, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Evenson. ADA: Michael Edward Nieskes DF ATTY: Jeremiah James Harrelson DF: Michael Henry Paul Merrill appeared. Case called at 4:25. ADA Nieskes updates the court. Atty. Harrelson agrees. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads NC to Ct 2 in 15CM434. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 2 in 15CM434. On motion of the State without objection, Crt dismisses Ct 1 in 15CM434. Sentencing arguments. DE makes statement. Court questions DE. Crt orders: Sentence Impose 45 days  with 45 days STAYED with the understanding the DE stays law abiding for 1 year. 
- Jail will be with huber for purposes of employment.
- credit for 3 days time served against any ultimate sentence. 
- DE to write a letter of apology to the officers involved to be to the court within 2 weeks from today. 
- $500 plus costs. ($943.00)
